# DAILY EXECUTION RULES

A repeatable routine so the work runs cleanly without constant supervision —
while keeping every guardrail in place.

## Daily caps
- **Contact forms: 5 per day, hard cap.**
- **Email: low and personal.** During domain warmup follow the ramp in
  `EMAIL-READY-CONTACT-STANDARDS.md` (start ~20–30/day). Never blast.
- One **follow-up only**, 7–10 days after first contact.

## Order of operations each day
1. **Opt-outs first.** Process any reply asking to stop → Opt-out = Yes. This
   comes before anything else, every day.
2. **Follow-ups due.** Open the tracker; send the single follow-up to anyone in
   the 7–10 day window who hasn't replied or opted out. Log the date.
3. **New contact — email.** A few personal emails to Direct-verified-public-email
   prospects, within the warmup ramp.
4. **New contact — forms.** Up to 5 contact-form submissions, official pages
   only, personalized first line. Log each.
5. **Research / queue building.** Add and bucket new prospects for tomorrow.
   Researching costs nothing and has no cap.

## Hard stops (do not push past these without a human decision)
- Daily caps reached → stop sending for the day; research only.
- A Gmail/form block → log it, pause, fix per the block-log file. Do not retry around it.
- Any opt-out or ToS prohibition → Blocked/no-contact, permanent.
- Anything touching credentials, billing, live ads/tracking, or production code → **stop and ask Gerry.**

## Weekly check
- Review opt-out rate and any block-log entries. If either is rising, reduce
  volume and tighten list quality before continuing.
